Title : Vidar Lønn-Arnesen
Text : [[File:68419_Vidar_Lønn-Arnesen.jpg|thumb|Vidar Lønn-Arnesen, 1967.]]
'''Vidar Lønn-Arnesen''' (born 22 June 1940) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] singer, radio presenter and television presenter.

He was born in [[Lardal]] and grew up in [[Horten]].<ref name=oyene>{{cite news|title=- Vi føler oss hjemme her, og er mer enn badegjester|last=Sørlie|first=Rune|date=12 August 2010|work=[[Øyene]]|pages=16–17|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He started his career as a local entertainer and [[pirate radio]] personality in the 1950s. From 1960 to 1964 he was a member of the pop group Tre Tainers.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Vidar Lønn-Arnesen|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=|location=|url=http://snl.no/Vidar_L%C3%B8nn-Arnesen|language=Norwegian|accessdate=4 May 2014}}</ref>

He was hired in the [[Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation]] in 1962. He presented the radio program ''[[Ti i skuddet]]'' from 1965 to 1970 and 1981 to 1991, and also ''Musikktelefonen'', ''Western Saloon'', ''[[Norsktoppen]]'' and ''Alle tiders blinkskudd''. From 1991 to 2001 he presented the television program ''Da Capo''.<ref name=snl/> He also hosted the [[Melodi Grand Prix]] in [[Norway in the Eurovision Song Contest 1972|1972]], [[Norway in the Eurovision Song Contest 1973|1973]], [[Norway in the Eurovision Song Contest 1974|1974]] and [[Norway in the Eurovision Song Contest 1977|1977]].

In 2010 he was decorated with the [[King's Medal of Merit|King's Medal of Merit in gold]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Fikk kongelig Lønn for strevet|author=Sæby, Inger-Marit Knap|publisher=[[Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation]]|date=22 June 2010|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He is married to television producer Tove Lønn-Arnesen<ref name=oyene/> and resides at [[Grav, Norway|Grav]].<ref name=ntb>{{cite news|title=70 år 22. juni: Programleder Vidar Lønn-Arnesen|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=9 June 2010|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

